                        <placeName key="place_111399">Fareham (Hampshire)</placeName>. <origDate when="1693">5 William and Mary. Feb. 22, 1693</origDate>. Indenture made between (1) Thomas Legh of Ridge Hall in Sutton, Cheshire,
                        esq., and Susannah his wife, the only sister and heir of William Gregg late
                        of Alkeston, Derbyshire, gent., and John Calvert of Beely, Derbyshire,
                        gent., and (2) Sir Brocas Gardiner of Roch Court, Hampshire, baronet,
                        reciting articles of agreement date 22 February 1692, being a confirmation
                        by (1) to (2) of possession of a coppice in the parish of Fareham,
                        Hampshire, assigned to (2) by a bargain and sale dated 21 February 1693 by
                        (1) to (2) (endorsed: Release Legh &amp; ux[or] &amp; Gardiner). .</p>
